    "title": "",
    "text": "In short: The new Northern Territory government has started fining parents who don’t get their children to school, in a bid to try to turn around woeful school attendance figures. Concerns have been raised that the policy is being rolled out without the “informed consent” of remote Aboriginal people, who are the main targets of the policy. What’s next? A group of community leaders have invited Education Minister Jo Hersey to \"come to Maningrida and engage with us directly about these changes\".",
